{"from":"manager","to":"eng-1-2","body":"TASK 9: Rewrite src/move_ordering.py + tests/test_move_ordering.py FROM SCRATCH\n\nThe current move_ordering.py in your worktree is BROKEN (old encoding, imports from src.board). DELETE it and write fresh.\n\nFIRST: git merge main (to get board.py, evaluation.py, and the cleaned-up main branch)\n\nThen DELETE the old files: rm src/move_ordering.py tests/test_move_ordering.py\n\nCreate NEW src/move_ordering.py:\n- Import from src.constants: EMPTY, PAWN, KNIGHT, BISHOP, ROOK, QUEEN, KING, piece_type, decode_from, decode_to, is_capture, is_promotion\n- Import Board from src.board\n\nPIECE_VALUE = {PAWN: 100, KNIGHT: 320, BISHOP: 330, ROOK: 500, QUEEN: 900, KING: 20000}\n\ndef order_moves(moves: list[int], board: Board, killer_moves: list, depth: int) -> None:\n    Sort in-place. Priority: captures (MVV-LVA) > killers > quiet moves.\n    MVV-LVA score = PIECE_VALUE[victim_type] * 10 - PIECE_VALUE[attacker_type]\n    Killer: killer_moves[depth] contains up to 2 non-capture moves that caused beta cutoff.\n\ndef order_captures(moves: list[int], board: Board) -> None:\n    Sort capture moves in-place by MVV-LVA score.\n\nCreate NEW tests/test_move_ordering.py:\n- test_mvv_lva_pxq_before_qxp: PxQ ranked higher than QxP\n- test_captures_before_quiet: captures sorted before quiet moves\n- test_killers_between_captures_and_quiet: killer moves rank above other quiet moves\n- test_order_moves_in_place: function returns None, modifies list\n- test_order_captures_in_place: function returns None, modifies list\n\nUse encode_move() from constants. Set up positions with Board(fen).\n\nRun: python -m pytest tests/test_move_ordering.py -v — ALL must pass.","msg_type":"assign","timestamp":1773174318}